properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 8 at 8:41PM CST until January 10 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southeast winds increasing to 20 to 30 knots later
tonight and Thursday morning with a few gusts to 33 knots. The
southeast winds will veer to the south by late Thursday morning
and southwest for Thursday evening. Waves building to 7 to 12
feet by sunrise.

* WHERE...Sheboygan to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 3 AM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 3 AM CST FRIDAY
